column3: 1. Communication: Does the main point come through?
column4: 2. Communication: Were the main ideas presented in an orderly and clear manner?
column5: 3. Communication: Did the talk maintain the interest of the audience?
column6: 4. Communication: Were the slides (or another instrument) appropriate and helpful to the audience?
column7: 5. Statistics: Statistical methods and/or critical thinking adequate?
column8: 6. Statistics: How well do the findings support the conclusions?
column9: 7. Project: States the objective, able to identify relevant questions
